HOC - Higher Order Component


It takes the one component as the Prop and return the one new 
component

const HOC = () => {
  const { Home } = props
  return (
    <> <Header /> {Home} <Footer /> </>
  )
}

Header 
Footer

<Header />

<Home /> 

<Footer />


Optimistic => unwanted code, component calling



Disadvantage of not using Optimistic code
1) Performance
2) Bundle Size




React Project(200MB) => bundle (2-3 KB)


